00:04:55,169 --> 00:04:57,672
and were amazed at the
response we received.

96
00:04:57,672 --> 00:05:00,633
Our crew expanded shooting
hundreds of hours of footage.

97
00:05:00,633 --> 00:05:02,218
We saw the effect the stigmas
had on the

98
00:05:02,218 --> 00:05:04,095
lives of countless
teens.

99
00:05:04,095 --> 00:05:06,097
These are the stories we wanted
to tell.

100
00:05:14,022 --> 00:05:15,565
I was in my mid-twenties,

101
00:05:15,565 --> 00:05:19,819
I had a good job, I was you
know... I kind of...

102
00:05:19,819 --> 00:05:21,988
I called it my mask life.
Everyone on the outside

103
00:05:21,988 --> 00:05:23,281
would think I was doing fine.

104
00:05:23,281 --> 00:05:25,033
I had a good job, I had a lot of
friends,

105
00:05:25,033 --> 00:05:26,701
I was involved in things

106
00:05:26,701 --> 00:05:28,536
on the inside I was miserable,

107
00:05:28,536 --> 00:05:31,247
and I really didn't share that
with anybody

108
00:05:31,247 --> 00:05:34,459
because I didn't trust
anybody enough to do that.

109
00:05:34,459 --> 00:05:37,045
I was content in my life,
there was no reason why

110
00:05:37,045 --> 00:05:38,546
I would
be unhappy.

111
00:05:38,546 --> 00:05:42,592
But there were these symptoms
that started to kind of overtake

112
00:05:42,592 --> 00:05:44,177
the way that I viewed myself,

113
00:05:44,177 --> 00:05:46,679
and also my future, and it was
uncharacteristic

114
00:05:46,679 --> 00:05:50,558
because I always was, and have
tried to be a very happy person,

115
00:05:50,558 --> 00:05:53,269
very positive and optimistic and
that's what people knew me as.

116
00:05:53,269 --> 00:05:55,980
So when I started to feel off,

117
00:05:55,980 --> 00:05:59,609
I didn't know how to
explain it to anyone

118
00:05:59,609 --> 00:06:01,360
I didn't know how to understand
it myself

119
00:06:01,360 --> 00:06:03,780
so I just didn't talk
about it

120
00:06:03,780 --> 00:06:06,199
and that was when I was 13.

121
00:06:06,199 --> 00:06:07,241
When I was depressed,

122
00:06:07,241 --> 00:06:11,079
I think my self-esteem got worse
cause everyone

123
00:06:11,079 --> 00:06:12,580
was telling me that I should
have been okay,

124
00:06:12,580 --> 00:06:14,665
and I was trying to be

125
00:06:14,665 --> 00:06:17,335
and I couldn't be and I felt
like a failure

126
00:06:17,335 --> 00:06:19,712
in that I couldn't do anything
right.

127
00:06:19,712 --> 00:06:22,507
And I remember sitting in my
apartment,

128
00:06:22,507 --> 00:06:24,801
at a window seat on
the third floor

129
00:06:24,801 --> 00:06:27,678
looking down, and I
really really considered

130
00:06:27,678 --> 00:06:29,097
jumping out the window that
night.

131
00:06:29,097 --> 00:06:30,932
I remember
that night vividly.

132
00:06:30,932 --> 00:06:33,601
I have had issues with
depression

133
00:06:33,601 --> 00:06:35,853
and cutting from when I was a
freshman in

134
00:06:35,853 --> 00:06:39,982
high school up until my
freshman year of college.

135
00:06:39,982 --> 00:06:41,859
I first started struggling with
depression

136
00:06:41,859 --> 00:06:44,237
when I was about
10 or 11 years old.

137
00:06:44,237 --> 00:06:49,826
I brought that with me into
college where things got worse

138
00:06:49,826 --> 00:06:53,371
because, you know, I was
separated from my family,

139
00:06:53,371 --> 00:06:59,627
my academic standards became...

140
00:06:59,627 --> 00:07:04,132
sort of... just a cloud,
constantly hanging over me.

141
00:07:04,132 --> 00:07:09,595
It got to the point where I was
cutting pretty much every day.

142
00:07:09,595 --> 00:07:11,639
In her book "The Bell Jar",

143
00:07:11,639 --> 00:07:15,518
Sylvia Plath talks about the
idea that

144
00:07:15,518 --> 00:07:21,149
depression and mental health
issues can act like a bell jar

145
00:07:21,149 --> 00:07:27,238
in which, it can descend at any
moment and you're trapped.

146
00:07:27,238 --> 00:07:32,160
There's the world outside, and
there's you inside and

147
00:07:32,160 --> 00:07:35,413
everything is distorted,
everything is suffocating and...

148
00:07:35,413 --> 00:07:37,874
and I'm still trying to work
through that.

149
00:07:37,874 --> 00:07:42,295
I was in middle school, so I
didn't really realize that

150
00:07:42,295 --> 00:07:45,131
I could have killed myself
accidentally with cutting.

151
00:07:45,131 --> 00:07:48,759
I never really thought about it,

152
00:07:48,759 --> 00:07:52,430
I just liked the pain and the
release.
